---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SubpageHeader from "../components/SubpageHeader.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<Layout title="About | MAE" description="About Morningside Art Exchange">
  <main class="blank-page about-page">
    <SubpageHeader title="ABOUT" />
    <section class="about-panel">
      <div class="about-panel__block">
        <p class="about-panel__eyebrow">Our Mission</p>
        <p>
          The Morningside Art Exchange (MAE) is a community-based arts collective
          currently operating in the Morningside Heights/Harlem area. We curate
          people-centered events designed to build connections through shared
          experience, connect artists to new target audiences, and create spaces
          oriented around joy, expression, growth, vision, and inspiration. Our artist
          network spans all mediums and senses, while vendors and performers work in
          fine art, clothing, pottery, music, wares, performance, literature, food,
          and more.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our goal is to foster community, collaboration, and curiosity for artists
          and creative individuals by creating accessible exhibition opportunities and
          meeting audiences where they are. We aim to change the narrative about art
          being pretentious and inaccessible by centering community over hierarchy,
          passion over profit, and growth over stagnance.
        </p>
      </div>

      <blockquote class="about-panel__statement">
        Morningside Art Exchange is a grassroots arts collective curating inclusive,
        sensory-driven events that connect artists with communities and challenge
        traditional art world hierarchies through joy, collaboration, and
        accessibility.
      </blockquote>

      <div class="about-panel__block">
        <p class="about-panel__eyebrow">Our Vision</p>
        <p>
          Looking to the future, we aim to grow beyond Columbia University and
          establish deeper roots within the broader artistic communities of
          Morningside Heights, Harlem, and the Upper West Side. Our vision is to
          become a leading hub for creative collaboration: offering design services to
          local businesses, curating cultural events that honor the area's rich
          history and legacy, and using art as a medium to advocate for and empower
          underserved communities.
        </p>
        <p>
          By breaking down the barriers between Columbia students and the neighborhood
          they inhabit, we will foster meaningful connections through shared
          experiences, new perspectives, and accessible, community-centered art.
        </p>
      </div>

      <blockquote class="about-panel__statement">
        We envision a future where art bridges divides, cultivating solidarity across
        Harlem, Morningside Heights, and the UWS by uplifting local voices, honoring
        neighborhood history, and transforming public spaces into platforms for
        expression and collective growth.
      </blockquote>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
